KB002 — How to Diagnose Slow Browsing
Purpose:  
Help technicians identify whether slow browsing is caused by DNS, connectivity, proxy settings, cache, or browser configuration.

🧭 Steps
Check DNS Resolution  
Run: Resolve-DnsName www.microsoft.com

Test Internet Connectivity  
Ping 8.8.8.8 and a website domain.

Check Proxy Settings  
Run: netsh winhttp show proxy

Check Browser Cache Size  
Large or corrupted cache slows page loads.

Test in Incognito Mode  
If it works → extension or profile issue.

Disable Extensions  
Ad blockers and password managers often cause issues.

